Sie flipped to an empty page and noted the date. Below it she wrote „11.5.648–13.12.648“.
„Are you stirring up old memories?“, inquired Ivory, looking at the old notebook. Kari nodded. „Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? There are only a few days left.“
Kari tapped twice on the lantern. „No“, as Ivory had expected. The Ice King never let Kari out, as he considered her a „flaw“. She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family, her siblings were all boys.
Similarly, Ivory was also affected. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed as if the world was changing. As punishment for this uniqueness, Ivory was given tasks where most of the time was spent alone.
Additionally, Ivory was forced to serve the princess. However, it didn't bother Ivory much, since Ivory also made a friend.
„You're almost turning a year older, right?“, asked Ivory, thinking about the fact that the princess would be turning a few days from now. Kari nodded with a sad flicker in her bright blue eyes.
„Would you like to celebrate your birthday?“, asked Ivory, thinking back to the last time the princess answered this question.
„No“, tapped Kari. Ivory knew this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. Ivory had been a baby at the time, but remembered how upset the servants and the citizens of the city had been. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen. And that she strangely could predict things that then actually happened.
„Well, what would you like to do?“, asked Ivory. Kari looked at Ivory excitedly. She was holding a piece of paper in her hand. On it was written:
15 x 15 cm canvas
White, various blue tones
Brushes in six different sizes
Easel
„These things are supposed to get them for you?“, said Ivory to the silent princess, whose braids swayed back and forth from her vigorous tapping. „Yes?“ Ivory giggled softly. The usually reserved princess showed so much excitement. It was the first time she had asked about something that had nothing to do with books and came from outside her room.
„Okay! Let's see each other later?“, asked Ivory, stood up and slung her way through the chaos of paper and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her blanket.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess had finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things outside her reach, like paints.
Ivory ran through the corridors again and tried to ignore the gossip of the maids.
„I've heard that she is supposed to be possessed by Queen Eirwen and therefore keeps going into this room.“
„I've heard that she eats children in this room.“
„She looks like a man, that's not normal, is it?“
Ivory covered her ears because she couldn't ignore the gossip anymore, and continued walking. The room of the royal painter was located in the eastern wing behind the second door on the left side.
Ivory approached the door, which was just as intricately decorated as Kari's door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six Original Dragons allegedly created by Frostfell. For a history-loving painter, the White Dragon on the door made perfect sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual mess. Paint splatters everywhere, brushes and paper scattered throughout the room, easels covering every inch of the wall. Unexpectedly, a different scene presented itself. The entire room was clean, and against a background of red velvet stood a chair. On the chair sat Crown Prince Aquilo, who was just being painted.
„Good morning, Ivory! Would you like to watch as your future king is painted?“, asked Aquilo and winked at Ivory.
„Excuse me, little prince“, said Ivory, mostly ignoring him and gathering the things the silent princess wished for. „I'm only here to get painting supplies.“
„My little girl wants to go already?“, asked Aquilo. „I want you to stay!“
„I don't want to stay.“ Ivory found the painting supplies on the list and put them in a box. „Besides, I'm not a girl.“
The prince was however of a different opinion. „Oh sweetie, that's just a phase! As you grow older, you'll outgrow it!“, he said indistinctly.
„I need to go“, said Ivory and felt uncomfortable by the prince's answer. All the ugly remarks he and others had made about Ivory's gender identity in the past came flooding back. I just want to get away from here.
„You're leaving already?“ Suddenly the prince appeared at the door and ignored the loud protests of the royal painter.
„That's not behavior for a future king!“, said Ivory.
„No one will find out. People won't believe you, and the painter will stay quiet if his life is worth anything.“ He briefly looked at the painter and then leaned closer to Ivory. „What do you think about a date?“ Ivory had been harassed before, but never by a prince, let alone the crown prince.
„Do you even know what the word «No» means?“, spat Ivory and pushed the crown prince away.
„No“, answered Aquilo with a smile. Of course, the crown prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word „No“ means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. „Why would you want to go out with someone like me? You must have at least 100 admirers?“
„Actually, it's 50“, interrupted him, still smiling. He pushed his hair back, which whirled in the cold air.
„Now you get it! Why me? I'm a danger to the palace.“ Ivory crossed her arms.
„You are the most beautiful girl I have ever seen.“ Aquilo lifted Ivory's chin with his finger and forced her to look at him.
